paragraphs.title: CODE
paragraphs.text:
%md
## Let's use Zeppelin Adaptor to explore data with Inter-Para Communication
* Before diving into this notebook make sure:
  * You have integrated [**Sample web logs**](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/kibana/7.8/getting-started.html#get-data-in)
  * You have used the **Introduction Notebook**
  * You have setup a [**python interpreter**](https://zeppelin.apache.org/docs/0.9.0-preview2/interpreter/python.html) & [**OpenSearch-SQL interpreter**](https://github.com/opensearch-project/dashboards-notebooks/blob/dev/docs/dev/Zeppelin_backend_adaptor.md#apache-zeppelin-setup)

msg.data:
Let’s use Zeppelin Adaptor to explore data with Inter-Para Communication

  • Before diving into this notebook make sure:
    • You have integrated Sample web logs
    • You have used the Introduction Notebook
    • You have setup a python interpreter & OpenSearch-SQL interpreter

paragraphs.title: CODE
paragraphs.text:
%md
## We'll use the pre-indexed sample web logs provided by OpenSearch Dashboards  
* Make an OpenSearch-SQL query 
* Import the output of SQL query in a python paragraph
* Plot an anomaly graph using python-matplot

paragraphs.title: Paragraph inserted
paragraphs.text:
%python.ipython

%matplotlib inline

import warnings
import numpy as np
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

logs = z.getAsDataFrame('data_logs')
agent_with_firefox = logs['agent'].str.count('Firefox').values
firefox_bytes = logs['bytes'].values[agent_with_firefox==1]

agent_with_chrome_safari = logs['agent'].str.count('Chrome').values
chrome_bytes = logs['bytes'].values[agent_with_chrome_safari==1]

agent_with_msie = logs['agent'].str.count('MSIE').values
msie_bytes = logs['bytes'].values[agent_with_msie==1]

print("Total Requests:", len(agent_with_firefox))
print("# Requests from Firefox Browser", np.sum(agent_with_firefox))
print("# Requests from Chrome/Safari Browser", np.sum(agent_with_chrome_safari))
print("# Requests from MSIE Browser", np.sum(agent_with_msie), "\n\n")

plt.figure(num=None, figsize=(30, 6))
plt.title("Request size for each browser")
plt.ylabel('Request Size in Bytes')
plt.xlabel('Requests made')
plt.axhline(y=10000, color='r', linestyle='--')
plt.plot(msie_bytes, 'ro', markersize=5, label="MSIE")
plt.plot(firefox_bytes, 'bo', markersize=5, label="Firefox")
plt.plot(chrome_bytes, 'go', markersize=5, label="Chrome")
plt.legend()
